Dear members of the West Seneca school community,

In order to provide a safe and meaningful educational experience, students in the West Seneca Central School District will begin the 2020-21 school year in a fully remote model of instruction. This will entail ALL students learning from home.

For your planning purposes, we have set a time frame for this model to be in place through the Thanksgiving Holiday.

View a message containing further details of this plan http://ow.ly/npFZ50AXu4s

The safety and well-being of our students is our top priority. Thank you.

In working with the Erie County Board of Elections, the district has experienced scan-ability issues with some of our ballots. As a result, we will need to tally these un-scanable ballots by hand. The Board of Elections is developing a computer program that will enable the district to accomplish this task in a systematic manner.

We have plans to complete this process ‪Friday evening‬, and will communicate results through the district website and livestream.

Additionally, the district has been utilizing the services of an independent auditor throughout this process and will continue to do so until it is complete.

Additionally, the district has been utilizing the services of an independent auditor throughout this process and will continue to do so until it is complete.

post_text: Thanks to A to Z Books, LLC, 600 coloring and activity books will be going home with West Seneca children in their daily breakfast and lunch pick-ups.
shared_text:
A to Z Books, LLC
May 4 at 9:02 AM ·

We said back in January that this year was going to be our #yearofgiving and we want to live up to our promise now more than ever. We never want to lose sight of who are and what we love doing, especially during hard times like these. So, we are VERY excited to be donating 600 assorted coloring books and activity books to West Seneca Central School District! The books are being delivered to the students with their free breakfast and lunches and we cannot wait for everyone to receive them! We hope the students enjoy the books and that they provide some fun activity time! Thanks in part to our friends at Dover Publications who helped make this possible.

#dogreatthings #donation #helpyourcommunity #beyourownkindofawesome #supportlocalbusiness #shoplocal #shopsmall #womanowned #buffalony #buffalove #indiebound #indiebookstore #buffalobookstores #booksconnectus #booksareessential Penguin Random House

post_text:
Dear members of the West Seneca school community,

Today, Gov. Andrew Cuomo extended our school closure for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. We will continue to provide our distance learning program for students for the duration of this closure. As we receive guidance from the state, an official end date for our distance learning program will be announced.

Additionally, we will continue with our food distribution and childcare programs for the duration of this closure. Plans for students to retrieve remaining personal belongings from schools will be communicated to families in the near future.

We wish all of the members of our school community good health and safety in these challenging times.

Additionally, we will continue with our food distribution and childcare programs for the duration of this closure. Plans for students to retrieve remaining personal belongings from schools will be communicated to families in the near future.

We wish all of the members of our school community good health and safety in these challenging times.

post_text:
Dear members of the West Seneca school community,

This morning the Buffalo News reported a confirmed case of COVID-19 in the town of West Seneca. We reached out to the Erie County Health Department to determine whether this case involved a connection to our schools. While the official at the health department was not able to provide specific information regarding this confirmed case due to health privacy laws, we were told that the district would have been notified had there been a connection to our schools. Therefore, we are under the assumption that there is no connection between our school system and this confirmed case. Best wishes to this individual on a full and speedy recovery. To all the families of our school community, please take care and stay safe.

Sincerely,

Matthew Bystrak
Superintendent of Schools

shared_text:
Legislator Joseph Lorigo
March 2 at 4:29 PM ·

I had the pleasure of visiting Allendale Elementary School this morning in celebration of Read Across America Day and Dr. Seuss's birthday. Thank you to Mrs. Kistner, Mrs. Nowinski, Mrs. Gallagher, Mrs. Slade, Mrs. Komosinski, and Mrs. Braunscheidel for having me read some classic Dr. Seuss stories to their classes. The students loved sharing all their favorite books, and I loved having the opportunity to read to them. As I told every class: Try and read something every single day!
text:
Legislator Joseph Lorigo
March 2 at 4:29 PM ·

I had the pleasure of visiting Allendale Elementary School this morning in celebration of Read Across America Day and Dr. Seuss's birthday. Thank you to Mrs. Kistner, Mrs. Nowinski, Mrs. Gallagher, Mrs. Slade, Mrs. Komosinski, and Mrs. Braunscheidel for having me read some classic Dr. Seuss stories to their classes. The students loved sharing all their favorite books, and I loved having the opportunity to read to them. As I told every class: Try and read something every single day!

shared_text:
Erie County School Nutrition Association
February 21 at 8:00 AM ·

Buffalo Public Schools and Frontier Central Schools were recently awarded Farm to School Grants from NYS Department of Agriculture and Markets! BPS will use their funding to integrate Farm to School programming in the classroom, cafeteria, and community by using a food truck to serve school lunches made with local ingredients to 16 high schools on a rotating basis. The food truck will also support culinary education. 🍅👩‍🌾👩‍🍳🚚

Frontier Central Schools will use their funding to develop a central kitchen to process, freeze, and store local foods. Hamburg Central School District - Hamburg, NY and West Seneca Central School District will also be able to use the processing kitchen.
text:
Erie County School Nutrition Association
February 21 at 8:00 AM ·

Buffalo Public Schools and Frontier Central Schools were recently awarded Farm to School Grants from NYS Department of Agriculture and Markets! BPS will use their funding to integrate Farm to School programming in the classroom, cafeteria, and community by using a food truck to serve school lunches made with local ingredients to 16 high schools on a rotating basis. The food truck will also support culinary education. 🍅👩‍🌾👩‍🍳🚚

Frontier Central Schools will use their funding to develop a central kitchen to process, freeze, and store local foods. Hamburg Central School District - Hamburg, NY and West Seneca Central School District will also be able to use the processing kitchen.
